##  ** About the role **

Our QLD State Government client is seeking an enthusiastic Cloud Engineer to
assist with the delivery of development and maintenance of high quality,
reliable, secure cloud platforms. The successful candidate will provide
authoritative, independent, and confidential advice in cloud development and
operations. You will work hands-on with the project team and business
operations teams to build and implement cloud solutions and support the
operations in the cloud.

##  ** Key responsibilities **

  * Provide input and guidance into application and product architecture and solution design discussions, contributing to the development of reliable, secure, and cost-efficient (whole of life) solutions. 
  * Provide advice to internal and external clients on cloud and DevOps principles, practices, and options. 
  * Provide technical advice to project teams on Azure infrastructure, architecture, design, and connectivity. 
  * Automate Azure resource provisioning and destruction with use of Azure Bicep or similar infrastructure-as-code orchestration tools. 
  * Provide technical expertise to lead key cloud areas such as Load Balancing, API Gateways, DBMSs, DNS configuration, Azure virtual networking, RBAC design, implementation, monitoring etc. 
  * Improve DevOps practices to create a robust configuration and integration framework. Leads CI/CD pipeline integration work in line with the agreed system and service design. 
  * Implement automation and orchestration and regularly review/optimize CI/CD processes and tools (across Azure) to reduce manual tasks, improve release cadence, predictability, reliability, repeatability, and quality. 
  * Implement metrics, monitor, and report on the results of integrations and builds, use infrastructure management tools to determine load and performance statistics and identify operational problems through metrics, contributing to their resolution. 

##  ** Skills and experience **

  * Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, or a related field. 
  * Proven experience (5 years) working as a Business Analyst, preferably in a technical environment. 
  * Strong analytical skills with the ability to critically evaluate information gathered from multiple sources, reconcile conflicts, decompose high-level information into details and distinguish user requests from underlying true needs. 
  * Solid understanding of software development methodologies and SDLC processes. 
  * Proficiency in creating clear and concise documentation, including business requirements documents (BRDs), functional specifications, use cases and process flow diagrams. 
  * Proven experience in the delivery of technology Cloud and SaaS projects. 
  * Familiarity with business intelligence (BI) tools, reporting tools and data visualization techniques. 
  * Relevant certifications such as CBAP (Certified Business Analysis Professional) or PMI-PBA (PMI Professional in Business Analysis) are preferred. 
  * Citizenship/visa: to be appointed to a position, you must be an Australian citizen, have permanent residency status or a visa permitting you to work in Australia. 
  * Implement platform controls in alignment with security policies, regulatory compliance and standards including IS18:2018 and ACSC Essential 8. 
  * Implement and utilise logging tools such as Log Analytics, Application Insights and Azure Monitor. 
  * Use security concepts such as Zero Trust, SIEM solutions, DevSecOps, encryption, PIM, IAM and PAM to secure and harden the cloud platform. 

##  ** Desirable **

  * Microsoft Azure DevOps Solutions Certifications 
  * Certified Cloud Security Professional 
  * Azure Security Engineer – Associate 

##  ** Benefits **

  * Initial 6-month contract with possible extension available 

  * Work for a large QLD State Government department 

  * Hybrid working arrangements from their Brisbane CBD location 

